---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Docs — xeto.dev">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">What is Xeto?</h1>

  <div class="mt-6 max-w-3xl space-y-5 text-ink-soft">
    <p>
      <strong class="text-ink">Xeto</strong> ("extensible explicitly typed
      objects") is a language for defining typed data specifications. A Xeto
      <em>spec</em> describes the shape of data — its slots, types, constraints,
      and documentation — and a Xeto <em>library</em> packages related specs
      together with versioning and dependencies.
    </p>
    <p>
      Think of it like a type system for the data layer: instead of every
      project inventing its own JSON conventions, domains share libraries of
      well-defined types that tooling can validate against, generate from, and
      document automatically.
    </p>
    <p>
      Xeto grew out of
      <a
        href="https://project-haystack.org"
        class="text-brand underline decoration-brand-soft underline-offset-2"
        >Project Haystack</a
      >
      and the smart-buildings world, where it types everything from HVAC points
      to ASHRAE control sequences — but the language itself is domain-neutral.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 class="mt-12 text-xl font-semibold">A taste of the language</h2>
  <pre
    class="mt-4 max-w-3xl overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-line bg-paper-soft p-5 text-sm"><code>// A person with typed slots
Person: Dict &#123;
  name: Str
  age: Int
  email: Str?        // maybe type — optional
&#125;

// Instance data validated against the spec
@brian: Person &#123;name: "Brian", age: 52&#125;</code></pre>

  <h2 class="mt-12 text-xl font-semibold">Learn more</h2>
  <ul class="mt-4 max-w-3xl space-y-2 text-ink-soft">
    <li>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/Project-Haystack/xeto"
        class="text-brand underline decoration-brand-soft underline-offset-2"
        >Xeto on GitHub</a
      > — source, core libraries, and language docs
    </li>
    <li>
      <a
        href="/explorer/"
        class="text-brand underline decoration-brand-soft underline-offset-2"
        >The explorer</a
      > — browse every spec in the registry libraries interactively
    </li>
  </ul>
</BaseLayout>
